Logistic regression is a statistical technique that utilizes the sigmoid function as its fundamental method. It is commonly employed in machine learning to construct models when the target variable is binary, such as determining whether a patient is deceased or alive [13, 69]. This algorithm is renowned for its simplicity in implementation, interpretation, and training. However, it tends to overfit when dealing with high-dimensional data and may struggle to capture intricate relationships [70]. The mathematical equation for logistic regression is as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
